517
00:38:26,330 --> 00:38:29,470
Doesn't it feel like your head cleared up for a second?

518
00:38:30,660 --> 00:38:34,230
- Has it?
- I tried it with my friend.

519
00:38:34,230 --> 00:38:36,160
Was he successful?

520
00:38:36,160 --> 00:38:38,920
No. It didn't work for him.

521
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:41,250
He has too many thoughts. He's got no chance.

522
00:38:41,250 --> 00:38:46,230
He needs a friend like me to talk it all out with him to clear his thoughts.

523
00:38:46,230 --> 00:38:49,900
- You're a good friend.
- What is this? What's going on?

524
00:38:49,900 --> 00:38:52,170
What's with your envious eyes and tone?

525
00:38:52,170 --> 00:38:55,260
Why are you being like that, when you've got so many friends?

526
00:38:55,260 --> 00:38:58,000
- Do you know me?
- No.

527
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:02,400
I heard rumors. Myeongil University's most popular person, Yeo Joon.

528
00:39:04,370 --> 00:39:07,300
I don't have any good friends.

529
00:39:07,300 --> 00:39:10,150
Honey! What are you doing?

530
00:39:10,150 --> 00:39:14,500
Then, let's catch up again next time.

531
00:39:28,830 --> 00:39:32,040
[Dorm: 600,000 won, Textbooks: 100,000 won, School Fees: 300,000 won, Living Expense: 300,000, Communication: 100,000 won]

532
00:39:36,180 --> 00:39:40,110
[Expenses: 1400,000 won]

533
00:40:08,500 --> 00:40:11,230
Don't lie just because I can't see you.

534
00:40:11,230 --> 00:40:13,840
I can see through your voice.

535
00:41:04,370 --> 00:41:06,120
You're already here!

536
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:08,330
I just got here.

537
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:11,200
You're here, Senior?

538
00:41:11,200 --> 00:41:14,840
Don't do this next time. I didn't ask you to be the group leader so that you could do things like this.

539
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:19,210
You could have just said that she worked hard. So haggardly.

540
00:41:19,210 --> 00:41:24,130
But he's right. You should ask me to do this stuff instead.

541
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:26,930
Whoever's early can do it.

542
00:41:26,930 --> 00:41:29,700
Have you contacted the other group members?

543
00:41:29,700 --> 00:41:33,270
Yes. They'll all be here on time.

544
00:41:38,620 --> 00:41:42,150
Hye Ji just said she can't make it because she's got the flu.

545
00:41:42,150 --> 00:41:45,320
I guess it'll just be the five of us today.

546
00:41:48,860 --> 00:41:52,510
[Design Meeting]

547
00:41:58,170 --> 00:42:01,910
It's only the first day, how could no one show up?

548
00:42:01,910 --> 00:42:05,070
This is your first time with a team assignment, isn't it? A core module class, not optional.

549
00:42:05,070 --> 00:42:06,780
Yes.

550
00:42:06,780 --> 00:42:12,770
On average, there are at least 3 group projects for your major. You end up hearing so many excuses.

551
00:42:12,770 --> 00:42:14,970
I think there are two types of people,

552
00:42:14,970 --> 00:42:18,770
Those with a sense of responsibility, and those without.

553
00:42:20,700 --> 00:42:25,930
Senior Jung Ho nor Senior Chun Gook are looking at their messages, and both are ignoring my phone calls.

554
00:42:25,930 --> 00:42:28,870
I should have confirmed with everyone.

555
00:42:30,030 --> 00:42:31,730
I'm sorry.

556
00:42:31,730 --> 00:42:36,290
The probability that a boat will go up a mountain will decrease when the number of boatmen decreases.
(T/N: Too many cooks spoil the soup.)

557
00:42:36,290 --> 00:42:40,730
Let's just divide the parts amongst us three first.

558
00:42:40,730 --> 00:42:42,760
Without the seniors?

559
00:42:42,760 --> 00:42:45,630
Will you just wait here for them?

560
00:42:45,630 --> 00:42:48,540
Then I'll just contact them separately to let them know their parts.

561
00:42:48,540 --> 00:42:51,740
Do you trust those people?

562
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:53,610
Pardon?

563
00:42:53,610 --> 00:43:00,080
Having expectations and getting disappointed make it harder to forgive. It's easier to not have any, to begin with.

564
00:43:01,950 --> 00:43:04,190
Senior, you're always so pessimistic.

565
00:43:04,190 --> 00:43:05,410
It's being realistic.

566
00:43:05,410 --> 00:43:09,220
I don't want to learn about that kind of reality.

567
00:43:09,840 --> 00:43:13,140
Oh, I guess if your reality is in the gutter,

568
00:43:13,140 --> 00:43:16,390
it could be difficult to be optimistic.

569
00:43:18,690 --> 00:43:20,430
I understand.

570
00:43:20,430 --> 00:43:22,150
Understand?

571
00:43:24,310 --> 00:43:25,960
Do you even know what it is to feel like you're in the gutter?

572
00:43:25,960 --> 00:43:30,220
I do. Not having money isn't the only gutter.

573
00:43:30,220 --> 00:43:33,970
Without knowing another's circumstances and acting as though you're the least fortunate,

574
00:43:33,970 --> 00:43:39,980
you're not... the type of person with a knife in his mouth, stabbing innocent people, are you?

575
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:44,670
Isn't that being too self-conscious?

576
00:43:49,310 --> 00:43:51,230
Leader...

577
00:43:51,230 --> 00:43:56,660
I'm the leader so I don't plan to give up on anyone.

578
00:43:56,660 --> 00:44:02,380
Let's divide the work into six parts, and if the rest don't do it, then I will.

579
00:44:07,930 --> 00:44:10,900
Then I have no choice but to back out.

580
00:44:14,120 --> 00:44:16,180
Senior!

581
00:44:16,950 --> 00:44:19,680
What do we do? If Senior Soo Hyun leaves then we're done for!

582
00:44:19,680 --> 00:44:22,430
Don't worry, Senior. I'll bring him.

583
00:44:29,620 --> 00:44:33,110
Senior, what happened? I've been trying to contact you this whole time.

584
00:44:33,110 --> 00:44:35,460
I was playing a couple of rounds of billiard...

585
00:44:35,460 --> 00:44:37,540
Senior, did you drink alcohol?

586
00:44:37,540 --> 00:44:39,070
We were playing for chicken and beer.

587
00:44:39,070 --> 00:44:42,330
You bastard, Nam Soo Hyun!

588
00:44:42,330 --> 00:44:46,310
Hey, what did you say about my age?

589
00:44:46,310 --> 00:44:47,320
Say it again.

590
00:44:47,320 --> 00:44:51,400
I told you, if you're 26, to act your age.

591
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:53,320
This bastard. He doesn't even know about seniority and is saying anything he wants.

592
00:44:53,320 --> 00:44:58,010
While you were out playing billiards and drinking alcohol, you were wasting the precious time of your juniors.

593
00:44:58,010 --> 00:45:00,380
Is that something a senior should be doing?

594
00:45:00,380 --> 00:45:03,410
This jerk! Do you want to die?

595
00:45:03,410 --> 00:45:05,460
You dodged?

596
00:45:05,460 --> 00:45:06,300
You won't come here?

597
00:45:06,300 --> 00:45:08,540
Bring it on, jerk. You're always acting up.

598
00:45:08,540 --> 00:45:10,880
Senior! Senior, you should let it go.

599
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:12,610
This is a school.

600
00:45:12,610 --> 00:45:13,570
Let go.

601
00:45:13,570 --> 00:45:15,030
What are you doing, not holding him back?

602
00:45:15,030 --> 00:45:17,980
Hey, hey, let him be. Nam Soo Hyun that bastard...

603
00:45:17,980 --> 00:45:18,860
- needs to get his head on straight.
- Senior!

604
00:45:18,860 --> 00:45:22,520
Senior, you're drunk right now. Don't cause trouble and just go home, okay?

605
00:45:22,520 --> 00:45:24,450
You're all crazy.

606
00:45:24,450 --> 00:45:26,210
Hey, Joon, you won't let go?

607
00:45:26,210 --> 00:45:27,930
One... two...

608
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:31,540
Come with me and Senior Chun Gook to have a few more drinks.

609
00:45:33,050 --> 00:45:35,200
Joon!

610
00:45:41,920 --> 00:45:44,990
Joon! Are you okay?

611
00:45:44,990 --> 00:45:48,770
Hey! Don't look down on me just because you have a bit of money.

612
00:45:48,770 --> 00:45:51,060
You think we don't know that you're talking about us behind our backs?

613
00:45:51,060 --> 00:45:53,350
Where do you think you're running away to!

614
00:45:56,820 --> 00:45:58,910
Don't hit him!

615
00:45:58,910 --> 00:46:01,590
You can just say it with words! Why are you hitting him!?

616
00:46:01,590 --> 00:46:04,070
I said don't hit him!

617
00:46:04,070 --> 00:46:06,020
Don't hit him...

618
00:46:16,430 --> 00:46:18,380
Yeo Joon...

619
00:46:20,030 --> 00:46:22,070
Don't hit...

620
00:46:55,100 --> 00:46:56,710
I'm fine.

621
00:46:56,710 --> 00:46:59,610
Just a moment It's all done.

622
00:47:05,730 --> 00:47:08,190
- Here...
- I'll do it.

623
00:47:13,550 --> 00:47:18,630
Joon... do you think he'll be okay on his own?

624
00:47:20,590 --> 00:47:23,580
If you're concerned, why don't you go look for him?

625
00:47:24,310 --> 00:47:26,790
I don't know where he lives.

626
00:47:28,690 --> 00:47:31,080
I'm getting up first. It's time for my part-time job.

627
00:47:31,080 --> 00:47:34,750
Senior...

628
00:47:34,750 --> 00:47:39,020
will you really be leaving the group project?

629
00:47:42,300 --> 00:47:45,760
You said that you would return the debt if the chance arose.

630
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:49,990
That debt... please return it now.

631
00:47:51,090 --> 00:47:53,310
Please don't leave.

632
00:47:53,310 --> 00:47:55,690
You're needed.

633
00:47:55,690 --> 00:47:58,990
Are you going to do the others' jobs if they mess everything up?

634
00:47:58,990 --> 00:48:01,160
As the team leader?

635
00:48:04,280 --> 00:48:08,820
No, I was mistaken about that.

636
00:48:08,820 --> 00:48:12,090
Grades should be based on your own contributions.

637
00:48:13,360 --> 00:48:17,350
All right, then I'll stay.

638
00:48:18,070 --> 00:48:20,670
Really?

639
00:48:20,670 --> 00:48:23,530
Just one more thing...

640
00:48:23,530 --> 00:48:25,810
It seems like I have quite the debt.

641
00:48:27,950 --> 00:48:32,090
Joon... he's not usually like that.

642
00:48:32,090 --> 00:48:34,610
I wonder what happened earlier.

643
00:48:35,500 --> 00:48:38,310
Please understand.

644
00:48:38,310 --> 00:48:41,590
Do you know what he's like usually?

645
00:48:41,590 --> 00:48:46,430
Well, Joon is usually all smiles and sociable.

646
00:48:46,430 --> 00:48:49,630
He doesn't seem like he acts too sensitive with others.

647
00:48:49,630 --> 00:48:52,090
I suppose you're right.

648
00:48:52,090 --> 00:48:57,070
But I can't listen to your request to understand him. That's not possible for me.

649
00:48:57,070 --> 00:48:58,580
I see...

650
00:49:03,980 --> 00:49:06,760
What's going to happen to our group...

651
00:49:34,190 --> 00:49:35,980
Get in.

652
00:49:36,880 --> 00:49:38,120
If you're going home.

653
00:49:38,120 --> 00:49:39,590
I can go on my own.

654
00:49:39,590 --> 00:49:41,420
Get in.

655
00:49:54,960 --> 00:49:58,890
Mom called me first, it wasn't me.

656
00:49:58,890 --> 00:50:01,660
I told you to tell me if you're going home.

657
00:50:01,660 --> 00:50:03,590
I don't want to.

658
00:50:05,520 --> 00:50:06,970
Why do I have to do that?

659
00:50:06,970 --> 00:50:09,450
Why do I have to get permission from you to go home?

660
00:50:09,450 --> 00:50:11,850
Because it's not your home.

661
00:50:12,750 --> 00:50:15,380
Then you're not my brother either.

662
00:50:16,800 --> 00:50:18,690
Put your seatbelt on.

663
00:51:18,620 --> 00:51:20,670
What do you mean by stupid?

664
00:51:20,670 --> 00:51:24,330
Unni, you're lucky your younger son has so much charm.

665
00:51:24,330 --> 00:51:27,970
And your older son is the country's youngest professor.

666
00:51:27,970 --> 00:51:31,210
You've raised both of your children well.

667
00:51:31,210 --> 00:51:33,630
Of course, you have to raise your own children well.

668
00:51:33,630 --> 00:51:37,160
TV doesn't capture all of Joon Wan's good looks.

669
00:51:37,160 --> 00:51:38,410
Yeah.

670
00:51:38,410 --> 00:51:41,430
Oh, by the way, our Chan Woo started at Seoul National University.

671
00:51:41,430 --> 00:51:43,170
He's Joon Wan's junior now.

672
00:51:43,170 --> 00:51:47,590
Just because you go to the same school, doesn't make you the same level.

673
00:51:50,880 --> 00:51:54,960
Joon, what department is it that you're in at Seoul University?

674
00:51:58,950 --> 00:52:02,120
I didn't get into Seoul University, I decided on Myeongil University...

675
00:52:02,120 --> 00:52:07,390
That's right! I was mistaken because everyone in our family went to Seoul National University.

676
00:52:07,390 --> 00:52:09,020
Sorry.

677
00:52:15,660 --> 00:52:17,650
Aunt, my school is nice!

678
00:52:17,650 --> 00:52:19,520
Joon Wan is also a professor there.

679
00:52:19,520 --> 00:52:24,260
Yeah, I thought he'd be a professor at Seoul National University or KAIST.

680
00:52:24,260 --> 00:52:25,980
Barely Myeongil University?

681
00:52:25,980 --> 00:52:27,940
Watch what you say.

682
00:52:29,940 --> 00:52:32,180
Dividing Seoul up and lining up the elite universities

683
00:52:32,180 --> 00:52:36,270
Be it Seoul University that I came out of and aunt's son went to or Joon's Myeongil university, all are from there to there.

684
00:52:36,270 --> 00:52:38,050
What do you mean they're the same!

685
00:52:38,050 --> 00:52:39,060
What nonsense.

686
00:52:39,060 --> 00:52:43,030
The standard of universities in our country all seems the same internationally.

687
00:52:43,030 --> 00:52:46,700
None of them stands out for their educational system.

688
00:53:06,930 --> 00:53:08,750
I have something urgent so I'll be heading out.

689
00:53:08,750 --> 00:53:09,790
Already?

690
00:53:09,790 --> 00:53:11,620
Let's go.

691
00:53:12,340 --> 00:53:16,110
Joon, you should stay a little longer. It's been quite a while.

692
00:53:16,110 --> 00:53:18,000
Come out.

693
00:53:18,000 --> 00:53:18,970
You go first.

694
00:53:18,970 --> 00:53:20,970
That's right, Joon Wan you go first.

695
00:53:20,970 --> 00:53:23,350
You said it was urgent.

696
00:53:23,350 --> 00:53:27,360
Go ahead first. Mom has probably been missing me.

697
00:53:27,360 --> 00:53:29,620
If I call, then leave.

698
00:53:40,960 --> 00:53:42,710
You're smiling?

699
00:53:42,710 --> 00:53:47,070
Is this funny? You smiled while talking about your school, didn't you?

700
00:53:47,070 --> 00:53:50,870
What's so great about attending a crap school like that for you to talk about it!?

701
00:53:50,870 --> 00:53:53,730
Joon Wan said he'd come back to pick him up.

702
00:53:53,730 --> 00:53:55,960
You're the problem, you are!

703
00:53:55,960 --> 00:53:59,030
Why did you call this useless fellow home and make him attend the family gathering?

704
00:53:59,030 --> 00:54:00,620
Do you even think!?

705
00:54:00,620 --> 00:54:01,900
Please don't be like this Dad.

706
00:54:01,900 --> 00:54:03,450
I was wrong.

707
00:54:03,450 --> 00:54:05,480
Shut your mouth.

708
00:54:06,470 --> 00:54:08,060
This jerk,

709
00:54:08,060 --> 00:54:11,780
don't let him appear in front of me! Do you understand!?

710
00:54:12,660 --> 00:54:15,010
Arrogant jerk.

711
00:54:22,820 --> 00:54:25,820
I'll leave now, Mom.

712
00:54:35,330 --> 00:54:37,240
Does it hurt?

713
00:54:37,240 --> 00:54:39,350
I'm fine.

714
00:54:39,350 --> 00:54:40,510
It doesn't hurt...

715
00:54:40,510 --> 00:54:43,600
Of course, it hurts. Why wouldn't it?

716
00:54:43,600 --> 00:54:45,810
You poor thing.

717
00:54:47,750 --> 00:54:49,690
Mom,

718
00:54:50,610 --> 00:54:53,200
I... I was wrong.

719
00:54:53,200 --> 00:54:56,270
- I interrupted the adult's conversation...
- No...

720
00:54:56,270 --> 00:54:58,590
it's my fault.

721
00:55:00,180 --> 00:55:05,290
It's my fault for believing that you would behave today.

722
00:55:05,290 --> 00:55:11,350
No... it's my fault for giving birth to you in the first place.

723
00:55:11,350 --> 00:55:13,190
What?

724
00:55:13,190 --> 00:55:16,630
But I did what I could for you.

725
00:55:16,630 --> 00:55:21,330
Look at Joon Wan. I gave birth to both of you, yet what's wrong with you?

726
00:55:21,330 --> 00:55:24,150
You should be as capable as your brother.

727
00:55:25,220 --> 00:55:28,970
Yes... I'm trying my best.

728
00:55:31,320 --> 00:55:33,750
You listen to me well.

729
00:55:33,750 --> 00:55:35,430
Yes.

730
00:55:38,750 --> 00:55:41,720
You're listening well.

731
00:55:53,090 --> 00:55:54,980
Mom!

732
00:55:55,700 --> 00:56:00,690
This is why I... hate you.

733
00:56:00,690 --> 00:56:03,830
Didn't I tell you to dye your hair black?

734
00:56:03,830 --> 00:56:06,190
I was in a rush and didn't have time.

735
00:56:06,190 --> 00:56:08,550
Don't lie! You've always been like that!

736
00:56:08,550 --> 00:56:11,010
I'll call the salon, so go right away.

737
00:56:11,010 --> 00:56:12,790
Okay.

738
00:56:14,210 --> 00:56:19,270
After saying "yes, yes," with a smile on your face, you'll probably just plan to fool us.

739
00:56:19,270 --> 00:56:20,990
That's what you're thinking, aren't you?

740
00:56:20,990 --> 00:56:21,830
No, Mom.

741
00:56:21,830 --> 00:56:26,610
Now that you've moved out, just how much more do you plan to deceive me?

742
00:56:26,610 --> 00:56:29,250
I'll really go.

743
00:56:29,250 --> 00:56:32,550
Where is the salon? I want to get it done by the stylist you use.

744
00:56:32,550 --> 00:56:34,680
Shut up.

745
00:56:36,650 --> 00:56:39,680
I'll really go, Mom.

746
00:56:39,680 --> 00:56:45,020
You are the sort who smiles widely while killing people inside.

747
00:56:45,020 --> 00:56:47,380
You think I don't know you?

748
00:56:50,560 --> 00:56:52,370
Take it.

749
00:56:56,920 --> 00:57:00,420
[Yeo Joon Wan]

750
00:57:01,680 --> 00:57:05,710
Yes, Brother? I'll be out.

751
00:57:08,760 --> 00:57:11,850
Don't make it obvious that you were hit, you know that right?

752
00:57:11,850 --> 00:57:14,360
Yes, I know.

753
00:57:15,310 --> 00:57:17,330
Mom...

754
00:57:19,090 --> 00:57:21,570
Please trust me a little bit.

755
00:57:21,570 --> 00:57:24,400
I'm twenty.

756
00:57:25,190 --> 00:57:27,550
Please trust me just a little.

757
00:57:31,190 --> 00:57:35,790
Leave, my Joon Wan is probably waiting for you.

758
00:57:50,880 --> 00:57:56,800
[Expenses]

759
00:58:01,310 --> 00:58:03,370
[Incoming call]
[010-9905-542]

760
00:58:04,940 --> 00:58:06,330
Hello?

761
00:58:06,330 --> 00:58:09,000
Hello, Senior?

762
00:58:09,000 --> 00:58:10,330
Who...?

763
00:58:10,330 --> 00:58:12,540
It's me.

764
00:58:15,790 --> 00:58:20,590
Even though you already know. You know everything.

765
00:58:20,590 --> 00:58:21,640
Did you drink alcohol?

766
00:58:21,640 --> 00:58:23,970
Yes.

767
00:58:23,970 --> 00:58:29,390
But I still want another drink. One with you Senior Nam Soo Hyun.

768
00:58:29,390 --> 00:58:31,130
Why would I drink with you?

769
00:58:31,130 --> 00:58:33,810
Don't be like that.

770
00:58:35,060 --> 00:58:40,560
I'll die today.

771
00:59:14,590 --> 00:59:17,990
Joon. Are you Yeo Joon?

